rComments: Funniest prof I've ever had; cares about student success; very helpful via email and office hours; very intelligent; very FAIR application based tests. Her tests aren't memorization-regurgitation, so typical psych majors think they're incredibly unfair; they weren't, they were just application based. Idk grade yet, but probs an A.

Her lectures are pretty clear and interesting. She's funny and makes the class enjoyable. The breakdown is a 20 percent paper, weekly quizzes, a midterm and a final. However, the marking for the course is pretty tough and exams are tricky. She can be pretty rude at times. Overall, not a bad prof.

Professor Uliaszeks class may seem easy.. its not. Shes a very tough grader and her exams are HARD. The questions are ambiguous leaving you to think maybe it could be all the answers. She uses lots of examples in class but sometimes she goes off on tangents. the weekly quizzes are designed to basically be a grade booster.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'EXTRA CREDIT', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: All i can say is.... MAD HARD EXAMS GL MY FRIENDS

While her sincerity towards students is questionable, she definitely knows her material and teaches the course VERY well. She used great examples to make things more applicable and understandable. The exams were VERY fair, even though people complained. Great lecturer - wish she taught more courses.

I really enjoyed this course. The professor used examples in everyday life which was interesting. She came to class even when heavily pregnant. Her exams were fair. The textbook was good. I would definitely recommend this class and Professor Uliaszek to anyone!

She knows the material, and simplifies the terminology well. However, the textbook was a lot of broad information that she should have gone over. She was not at all empathetic towards students, especially on the assignment. Make sure you download lectures before class, as she takes them off fast! Id reccomend the class, but with a different prof.
Great prof, really cares about students! Not a bird course but very important and interesting if you're serious about clinical psychology. Exams were alright. I highly recommend!
She's a great lecturer, and is very competent in the material--which is really interesting! Her personality, however, needs to be adjusted.
Never take a class with her, very hard marker and her exam questions are worded poorly. If any other prof was teaching this course it would be better!!! Should never teach a class again.

horrible prof. not at all empathetic. lectures are broad and vague and this makes it hard to study for the exams, which are detailed and specific. the TA was a better teacher than her. I would never take a class with her again. dont take the course unless you need to, my words of advice

Very interesting course and well taught. But if you want a professor that's extremely moody, barely smiles, very clearly plays favourites with students, is difficult to approach, and is sometimes very rude, then take the course. If not, don't bother. :)
Intelligent & practical. I learned a lot that I could apply to my own life from her. She's a real professional. Just make sure to always attend lecs. Very important for exams.
Intelligent professor, very expirienced. Shes quite professional and it's impressive how practically she teaches. Exams are lecture based (specifics) and some text. She's an amazing person.
You could say she's nice, but she's also strict and moody at times. talks fast with funny pronunciations on certain words.
Interesting course.  The prof is clearly competent on this subject but is sometimes too serious and can lighten up a bit.  Overall, she did an alright job.

About 95% of the exams are things she literally said during lectures. Only about 5% are things that are exclusively from the book, if anything at all. The book is used as a suplement. The course is very stright-forward, not difficult material. She likes to keep students engaged by having conversations about topics in class. Overall good prof
